{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872073842,"sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","part":{"id":"prt_d7a394d78001f171ayvHaALVLB","messageID":"msg_d7a393afb001htqHlJh35Bi4lM","sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n13: в”Ӯ                    PicoD API Layer                       в”Ӯ\n14: в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\n15: в”Ӯ  CommandExecutor  в”Ӯ  ExecutionManager  в”Ӯ  OutputBuffer  в”Ӯ\n16: в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\n17: в”Ӯ              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  в”Ӯ\n18: в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\n19: в”Ӯ              Resource Limiter (Integration)              в”Ӯ\n20: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Key Interfaces\n24: \n25: #### CommandExecutor\n26: \n27: The primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n28: \n29: ```go\n30: type CommandExecutor interface {\n31:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n32:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n33:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n34:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n35:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: #### ExecutionRequest\n40: \n41: Configuration for a command execution.\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n45:     Command     string\n46:     Args        []string\n47:     WorkingDir  string\n48:     Environment map[string]string\n49:     Timeout     time.Duration\n50:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n51:     SessionID   string\n52: }\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### ExecutionResult\n56: \n57: Result of a command execution.\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: type ExecutionResult struct {\n61:     ID         ExecutionID\n62:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n63:     ExitCode   int\n64:     Stdout     []byte\n65:     Stderr     []byte\n66:     StartedAt  time.Time\n67:     FinishedAt time.Time\n68:     Error      *ExecutionError\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: ### Synchronous Execution\n75: \n76: ```\n77: 1. Client calls Execute()\n78: 2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n79: 3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n80: 4. Command is executed with monitoring\n81: 5. Output is captured\n82: 6. Result is returned to client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Asynchronous Execution\n86: \n87: ```\n88: 1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n89: 2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n90: 3. Background worker picks up execution\n91: 4. Status updates to \"running\"\n92: 5. Output is streamed to buffer\n93: 6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n94: 7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Error Handling\n98: \n99: ### Error Types\n100: \n101: - `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n102: - `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n103: - `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n104: - `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n105: - `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n106: - `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n107: \n108: ### Status States\n109: \n110: ```\n111: pending вҶ’ running вҶ’ completed\n112:               вҶ“\n113:             failed\n114:               вҶ“\n115:            cancelled\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Security Considerations\n119: \n120: - Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n121: - Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n122: - No direct shell access\n123: - Environment variable filtering\n124: - Working directory restrictions\n125: \n126: ## Performance Considerations\n127: \n128: - Connection pooling to sandbox service\n129: - Output buffering with size limits\n130: - Concurrent execution limits\n131: - Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n132: \n133: ## Open Questions\n134: \n135: 1. Maximum output size limits?\n136: 2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n137: 3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n138: 4. Execution queue prioritization?\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    PicoD API Layer                       в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ  CommandExecutor  в”Ӯ  ExecutionManager  в”Ӯ  OutputBuffer  в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  в”Ӯ\nв”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\nв”Ӯ              Resource Limiter (Integration)              в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775872073800,"end":1775872073839}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872073844,"sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","part":{"id":"prt_d7a395220001hT0b5cVOYRouNG","messageID":"msg_d7a393afb001htqHlJh35Bi4lM","sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-015  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n10: \n11: The PicoD Command Execution API provides a high-level interface for executing commands in sandbox environments. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution, with features including resource limits, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: CommandExecutor Interface\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a `CommandExecutor` interface that supports synchronous execution, asynchronous execution, status retrieval, cancellation, and output streaming.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Execute runs command synchronously\n22: - **GIVEN** a valid `CommandExecutor` instance\n23: - **AND** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"echo\"`, `Args=[\"hello\"]`\n24: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL validate the request\n26: - **AND** execute the command in the sandbox\n27: - **AND** capture stdout and stderr\n28: - **AND** return an `ExecutionResult` with `ExitCode=0`, `Stdout=[]byte(\"hello\\n\")`\n29: - **AND** return `nil` error on successful execution\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Execute returns error on invalid request\n32: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with empty `Command=\"\"`\n33: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n34: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n35: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating command is required\n36: - **AND** SHALL NOT attempt sandbox execution\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Execute returns error on timeout\n39: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"sleep\"`, `Args=[\"60\"]`, `Timeout=1s`\n40: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n41: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n42: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL start the command\n43: - **AND** when timeout expires, cancel the execution\n44: - **AND** return an error indicating timeout occurred\n45: - **AND** the result SHALL have `Status.State=StateFailed`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: ExecuteAsync queues command for background execution\n48: - **GIVEN** a valid `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"long-running-task\"`\n49: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n50: - **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync(ctx, req)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL generate a unique `ExecutionID`\n52: - **AND** persist initial status with `State=StatePending`\n53: - **AND** queue the execution for background processing\n54: - **AND** return the `ExecutionID` immediately\n55: - **AND** return `nil` error\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: ExecuteAsync validates request before queuing\n58: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `WorkingDir=\"/nonexistent/path\"`\n59: - **AND** the working directory does not exist in sandbox\n60: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n61: - **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync(ctx, req)` is called\n62: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL validate the request\n63: - **AND** return an error indicating working directory is invalid\n64: - **AND** SHALL NOT queue the execution\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: GetStatus returns current execution status\n67: - **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-abc123\"` exists with `State=StateRunning`\n68: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n69: - **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-abc123\")` is called\n70: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL query the status store\n71: - **AND** return an `ExecutionStatus` with `State=StateRunning`\n72: - **AND** return `nil` error\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: GetStatus returns completed status\n75: - **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-completed\"` has finished with exit code 0\n76: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n77: - **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-completed\")` is called\n78: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ExecutionStatus` with:\n79:   - `State=StateCompleted`\n80:   - `ExitCode=*0` (pointer to 0)\n81:   - `FinishedAt` set to completion time\n82: - **AND** return `nil` error\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: GetStatus returns error for non-existent execution\n85: - **GIVEN** no execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-nonexistent\"` exists\n86: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n87: - **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, \"exec-nonexistent\")` is called\n88: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionNotFound`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Cancel stops a running execution\n91: - **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-running\"` with `State=StateRunning`\n92: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n93: - **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, \"exec-running\")` is called\n94: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL signal the sandbox to terminate the process\n95: - **AND** update status to `State=StateCancelled`\n96: - **AND** return `nil` error\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Cancel returns error for already completed execution\n99: - **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-done\"` with `State=StateCompleted`\n100: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n101: - **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, \"exec-done\")` is called\n102: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: StreamOutput returns output channel for running execution\n105: - **GIVEN** an execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-streaming\"` with `State=StateRunning`\n106: - **AND** the execution is producing output\n107: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n108: - **WHEN** `StreamOutput(ctx, \"exec-streaming\")` is called\n109: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a `<-chan OutputChunk` channel\n110: - **AND** the channel SHALL receive chunks as output is produced\n111: - **AND** the channel SHALL be closed when execution completes\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: StreamOutput returns error for non-existent execution\n114: - **GIVEN** no execution with `ExecutionID=\"exec-missing\"` exists\n115: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n116: - **WHEN** `StreamOutput(ctx, \"exec-missing\")` is called\n117: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrExecutionNotFound`\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: ExecutionRequest Validation\n122: \n123: The system SHALL validate `ExecutionRequest` fields and reject invalid configurations before execution.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Empty command is rejected\n126: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"\"`\n127: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n128: - **WHEN** any execution method is called with this request\n129: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidCommand: command is required`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Command with path traversal is rejected\n132: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"../../../etc/passwd\"`\n133: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n134: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n135: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error indicating command contains invalid characters\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: WorkingDir outside allowed paths is rejected\n138: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `WorkingDir=\"/etc\"`\n139: - **AND** allowed working directories are restricted to `/workspace/*`\n140: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n141: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n142: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidWorkingDir: working directory not allowed`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Environment variable names are validated\n145: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Environment={\"INVALID-NAME\": \"value\"}`\n146: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n147: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n148: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error indicating invalid environment variable name\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: SessionID is required for sandbox resolution\n151: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `SessionID=\"\"`\n152: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n153: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n154: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return error `ErrInvalidSessionID: session ID is required`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Resource Constraints Enforcement\n159: \n160: The system SHALL enforce resource limits on command executions through sandbox integration.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Memory limit is enforced\n163: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxMemory=104857600` (100MB)\n164: - **AND** the command attempts to allocate 200MB\n165: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n166: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n167: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL enforce the memory limit\n168: - **AND** the execution SHALL be terminated with `ExitCode != 0`\n169: - **AND** the result SHALL have `Error.Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"`\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: CPU limit is enforced\n172: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxCPU=50.0` (50%)\n173: - **AND** the command is CPU-intensive\n174: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n175: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n176: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL throttle CPU usage to 50%\n177: - **AND** execution SHALL complete within timeout\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: File descriptor limit is enforced\n180: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxFiles=10`\n181: - **AND** the command attempts to open 20 files\n182: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n183: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n184: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL return error on file open exceeding limit\n185: - **AND** `Error.Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"` with details about file limit\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: IO bandwidth limit is enforced\n188: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `ResourceLimits.MaxIOBytes=1048576` (1MB/s)\n189: - **AND** the command performs heavy IO operations\n190: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n191: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n192: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL throttle IO to 1MB/s\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### Requirement: Execution Status Management\n197: \n198: The system SHALL maintain execution status through state transitions and persist status in the store.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Status transitions from pending to running\n201: - **GIVEN** an async execution is queued with `State=StatePending`\n202: - **WHEN** the background worker picks up the execution\n203: - **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateRunning`\n204: - **AND** `StartedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Status transitions from running to completed\n207: - **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n208: - **AND** the command completes with exit code 0\n209: - **WHEN** the execution finishes\n210: - **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateCompleted`\n211: - **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be set to 0\n212: - **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Status transitions from running to failed\n215: - **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n216: - **AND** the command exits with non-zero code\n217: - **WHEN** the execution finishes\n218: - **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateFailed`\n219: - **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be set to the actual exit code\n220: - **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to current time\n221: - **AND** `Error` SHALL contain failure details\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Status transitions to cancelled\n224: - **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateRunning`\n225: - **WHEN** `Cancel()` is called\n226: - **THEN** the status SHALL be updated to `State=StateCancelled`\n227: - **AND** `FinishedAt` SHALL be set to cancellation time\n228: - **AND** `ExitCode` SHALL be nil or reflect termination signal\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Terminal states are immutable\n231: - **GIVEN** an execution with `State=StateCompleted`\n232: - **WHEN** any status update is attempted\n233: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL reject the update\n234: - **AND** return error indicating execution is in terminal state\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: Output Capture and Streaming\n239: \n240: The system SHALL capture command output (stdout/stderr) and support real-time streaming.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Output is captured for sync execution\n243: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Command=\"echo\"`, `Args=[\"stdout\"]`, stdout redirected\n244: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n245: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n246: - **THEN** the `ExecutionResult.Stdout` SHALL contain `[]byte(\"stdout\\n\")`\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Stderr is captured separately\n249: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` that writes to stderr\n250: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n251: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n252: - **THEN** the `ExecutionResult.Stderr` SHALL contain the error output\n253: - **AND** `ExecutionResult.Stdout` SHALL be empty or contain stdout only\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Output size limit is enforced\n256: - **GIVEN** configuration `max_output_size=1MB`\n257: - **AND** a command that produces 10MB of output\n258: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n259: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n260: - **THEN** output capture SHALL be truncated at 1MB\n261: - **AND** `ExecutionResult` SHALL indicate truncation occurred\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: StreamOutput delivers chunks in order\n264: - **GIVEN** an async execution is running and producing output\n265: - **AND** a client calls `StreamOutput(ctx, id)`\n266: - **WHEN** the command writes \"line1\\nline2\\n\"\n267: - **THEN** the channel SHALL receive `OutputChunk{Data: []byte(\"line1\\n\"), Type: Stdout}`\n268: - **AND** then `OutputChunk{Data: []byte(\"line2\\n\"), Type: Stdout}`\n269: - **AND** chunks SHALL be in order of production\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: StreamOutput context cancellation stops streaming\n272: - **GIVEN** a client is streaming output from an execution\n273: - **AND** the client cancels the context\n274: - **WHEN** the context cancellation is detected\n275: - **THEN** the output channel SHALL be closed\n276: - **AND** the streaming goroutine SHALL exit cleanly\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Output buffering respects buffer size limits\n279: - **GIVEN** configuration `output_buffer_size=4KB`\n280: - **AND** a command producing continuous output\n281: - **WHEN** output exceeds 4KB\n282: - **THEN** older output SHALL be discarded or flushed to store\n283: - **AND** buffer SHALL not exceed configured size\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ### Requirement: Error Handling and Error Types\n288: \n289: The system SHALL define and return appropriate error types for different failure scenarios.\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: ErrInvalidRequest for malformed requests\n292: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with invalid fields\n293: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n294: - **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrInvalidRequest`\n295: - **AND** the error message SHALL describe which field is invalid\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: ErrResourceExceeded for resource limit violations\n298: - **GIVEN** an execution that exceeds memory limits\n299: - **WHEN** the sandbox terminates the process\n300: - **THEN** the result SHALL contain `Error` with `Code=\"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"`\n301: - **AND** `Error.Message` SHALL indicate which resource was exceeded\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: ErrTimeout for execution timeout\n304: - **GIVEN** an execution with `Timeout=5s`\n305: - **AND** the command runs longer than 5 seconds\n306: - **WHEN** timeout occurs\n307: - **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrTimeout`\n308: - **AND** `ExecutionStatus.State` SHALL be `StateFailed`\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: ErrSandboxUnavailable when sandbox is not accessible\n311: - **GIVEN** a `SessionID` that resolves to an unreachable sandbox\n312: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n313: - **THEN** the error SHALL be `ErrSandboxUnavailable`\n314: - **AND** the error SHALL include sandbox identification details\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: ErrExecutionFailed for non-zero exit codes\n317: - **GIVEN** a command that exits with code 1\n318: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` completes\n319: - **THEN** the result SHALL have `ExitCode=1`\n320: - **AND** the error SHALL be `ErrExecutionFailed` with exit code in details\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: ErrCancelled for cancelled executions\n323: - **GIVEN** a running execution\n324: - **WHEN** `Cancel(ctx, id)` is called\n325: - **THEN** the status SHALL be `StateCancelled`\n326: - **AND** subsequent calls to `GetStatus` SHALL indicate cancellation\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: Integration with Sandbox Interface\n331: \n332: The system SHALL integrate with the sandbox interface (AR-009) for actual command execution.\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Sandbox is resolved by SessionID\n335: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `SessionID=\"sess-abc123\"`\n336: - **AND** session `\"sess-abc123\"` exists in the store with sandbox info\n337: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n338: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n339: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL query the store for sandbox info\n340: - **AND** resolve the sandbox endpoint from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: Sandbox connection failures are handled\n343: - **GIVEN** a valid `SessionID` pointing to a sandbox\n344: - **AND** the sandbox pod is not responding\n345: - **AND** a `CommandExecutor` instance\n346: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n347: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrSandboxUnavailable`\n348: - **AND** the error SHALL include the connection failure reason\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: Sandbox environment variables are merged\n351: - **GIVEN** an `ExecutionRequest` with `Environment={\"FOO\": \"bar\"}`\n352: - **AND** the sandbox has default environment variables\n353: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n354: - **THEN** the request environment SHALL override sandbox defaults\n355: - **AND** merged environment SHALL be passed to the sandbox\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ### Requirement: Integration with Status Store\n360: \n361: The system SHALL persist execution status and metadata using the store interface (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014).\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: Execution status is persisted on state change\n364: - **GIVEN** an async execution transitions from `StatePending` to `StateRunning`\n365: - **WHEN** the state change occurs\n366: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `store.UpdateStatus(ctx, status)`\n367: - **AND** the update SHALL succeed before acknowledging the transition\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Store failures are handled gracefully\n370: - **GIVEN** an execution completes successfully\n371: - **AND** the store is temporarily unavailable\n372: - **WHEN** status update is attempted\n373: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL log the error\n374: - **AND** return the execution result to the caller\n375: - **AND** status MAY be inconsistent (documented limitation)\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Output is stored for later retrieval\n378: - **GIVEN** a completed execution with captured output\n379: - **WHEN** the execution finishes\n380: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL store output in the store\n381: - **AND** subsequent `GetStatus` calls SHALL include output reference\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ### Requirement: ExecutionID Generation\n386: \n387: The system SHALL generate unique execution identifiers for tracking.\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: ExecutionID is unique per execution\n390: - **GIVEN** multiple `ExecuteAsync` calls\n391: - **WHEN** each call returns an `ExecutionID`\n392: - **THEN** all returned IDs SHALL be unique\n393: - **AND** no two executions SHALL share the same ID\n394: \n395: #### Scenario: ExecutionID format is valid\n396: - **GIVEN** an execution is queued\n397: - **WHEN** `ExecuteAsync` returns\n398: - **THEN** the `ExecutionID` SHALL match pattern `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`\n399: - **AND** length SHALL be between 8 and 64 characters\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ### Requirement: Context Cancellation Handling\n404: \n405: The system SHALL respect context cancellation and clean up resources appropriately.\n406: \n407: #### Scenario: Execute cancels on context cancellation\n408: - **GIVEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is running\n409: - **AND** the context is cancelled\n410: - **WHEN** cancellation is detected\n411: - **THEN** the execution SHALL be terminated\n412: - **AND** error `ErrCancelled` SHALL be returned\n413: \n414: #### Scenario: GetStatus returns error on cancelled context\n415: - **GIVEN** a cancelled context\n416: - **WHEN** `GetStatus(ctx, id)` is called\n417: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return the context error\n418: - **AND** SHALL NOT query the store\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Cleanup on context cancellation\n421: - **GIVEN** an async execution is streaming output\n422: - **AND** the context is cancelled\n423: - **WHEN** cancellation propagates\n424: - **THEN** all goroutines SHALL exit\n425: - **AND** channels SHALL be closed\n426: - **AND** no goroutine leaks SHALL occur\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ### Requirement: Concurrent Execution Limits\n431: \n432: The system SHALL enforce limits on concurrent command executions.\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Concurrent limit is enforced\n435: - **GIVEN** configuration `max_concurrent_executions=10`\n436: - **AND** 10 executions are currently running\n437: - **WHEN** an 11th execution is requested\n438: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL queue the request\n439: - **OR** return `ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions`\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: Queued execution starts when slot available\n442: - **GIVEN** `max_concurrent_executions=5`\n443: - **AND** 5 executions are running\n444: - **AND** 3 executions are queued\n445: - **WHEN** one running execution completes\n446: - **THEN** the first queued execution SHALL start\n447: - **AND** its status SHALL transition to `StateRunning`\n448: \n449: ---\n450: \n451: ### Requirement: Configuration\n452: \n453: The system SHALL read PicoD configuration from environment variables.\n454: \n455: #### Scenario: Default timeout is applied\n456: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=30s`\n457: - **AND** an `ExecutionRequest` with no `Timeout` set\n458: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n459: - **THEN** the default timeout of 30s SHALL be applied\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Max output size is configurable\n462: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE=5MB`\n463: - **AND** a command producing large output\n464: - **WHEN** `Execute(ctx, req)` is called\n465: - **THEN** output SHALL be limited to 5MB\n466: \n467: #### Scenario: Max concurrent executions is configurable\n468: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT=50`\n469: - **WHEN** the `CommandExecutor` is initialized\n470: - **THEN** the concurrent execution limit SHALL be set to 50\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Changes to Base Specification\n475: \n476: No modifications to existing interfaces. This AR introduces new functionality in the `pkg/picod` module.\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## New Interfaces\n481: \n482: ### CommandExecutor Interface\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: package picod\n486: \n487: import \"context\"\n488: \n489: // CommandExecutor defines the interface for executing commands in sandboxes.\n490: type CommandExecutor interface {\n491:     // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n492:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n493:     \n494:     // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n495:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n496:     \n497:     // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n498:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n499:     \n500:     // Cancel stops a running execution.\n501:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n502:     \n503:     // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n504:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n505: }\n506: ```\n507: \n508: ### Execution Types\n509: \n510: ```go\n511: // ExecutionID uniquely identifies a command execution.\n512: type ExecutionID string\n513: \n514: // ExecutionRequest contains parameters for command execution.\n515: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n516:     Command        string\n517:     Args           []string\n518:     WorkingDir     string\n519:     Environment    map[string]string\n520:     Timeout        time.Duration\n521:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n522:     SessionID      string\n523: }\n524: \n525: // ExecutionResult contains the result of a command execution.\n526: type ExecutionResult struct {\n527:     ID         ExecutionID\n528:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n529:     ExitCode   int\n530:     Stdout     []byte\n531:     Stderr     []byte\n532:     StartedAt  time.Time\n533:     FinishedAt time.Time\n534:     Error      *ExecutionError\n535: }\n536: \n537: // ExecutionStatus represents the current state of an execution.\n538: type ExecutionStatus struct {\n539:     ID         ExecutionID\n540:     State      ExecutionState\n541:     StartedAt  *time.Time\n542:     FinishedAt *time.Time\n543:     ExitCode   *int\n544: }\n545: \n546: // ExecutionState represents the state of command execution.\n547: type ExecutionState string\n548: \n549: const (\n550:     StatePending   ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n551:     StateRunning   ExecutionState = \"running\"\n552:     StateCompleted ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n553:     StateFailed    ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n554:     StateCancelled ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n555: )\n556: \n557: // ResourceConstraints defines resource limits for execution.\n558: type ResourceConstraints struct {\n559:     MaxMemory  int64   // bytes\n560:     MaxCPU     float64 // percentage (0-100)\n561:     MaxIOBytes int64   // bytes per second\n562:     MaxFiles   int     // max open file descriptors\n563: }\n564: \n565: // ExecutionError contains detailed error information.\n566: type ExecutionError struct {\n567:     Code    string\n568:     Message string\n569:     Details map[string]interface{}\n570: }\n571: \n572: // OutputChunk represents a piece of output from a command.\n573: type OutputChunk struct {\n574:     Data      []byte\n575:     Type      OutputType\n576:     Timestamp time.Time\n577: }\n578: \n579: // OutputType indicates the source of output.\n580: type OutputType string\n581: \n582: const (\n583:     Stdout OutputType = \"stdout\"\n584:     Stderr OutputType = \"stderr\"\n585: )\n586: \n587: // ExecutorOptions contains configuration for CommandExecutor.\n588: type ExecutorOptions struct {\n589:     DefaultTimeout         time.Duration\n590:     MaxConcurrentExecutions int\n591:     MaxOutputSize          int64\n592:     OutputBufferSize       int\n593: }\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ### Error Types\n597: \n598: ```go\n599: var (\n600:     ErrInvalidRequest               = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n601:     ErrInvalidCommand               = errors.New(\"picod: command is required\")\n602:     ErrInvalidSessionID             = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n603:     ErrInvalidWorkingDir            = errors.New(\"picod: invalid working directory\")\n604:     ErrResourceExceeded             = errors.New(\"picod: resource limits exceeded\")\n605:     ErrTimeout                      = errors.New(\"picod: execution timeout\")\n606:     ErrSandboxUnavailable           = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n607:     ErrExecutionFailed              = errors.New(\"picod: execution failed\")\n608:     ErrExecutionNotFound            = errors.New(\"picod: execution not found\")\n609:     ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete     = errors.New(\"picod: execution already complete\")\n610:     ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions  = errors.New(\"picod: too many concurrent executions\")\n611:     ErrCancelled                    = errors.New(\"picod: execution cancelled\")\n612: )\n613: ```\n614: \n615: ---\n616: \n617: ## Modified Interfaces\n618: \n619: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## Behavioral Changes\n624: \n625: | Behavior | Before | After |\n626: |----------|--------|-------|\n627: | Command execution | Direct sandbox calls | Through PicoD API with resource limits |\n628: | Execution tracking | No persistence | Persistent status in store |\n629: | Output handling | Direct capture | Buffered, size-limited capture |\n630: | Cancellation | Not supported | Supported via Cancel() API |\n631: | Streaming | Not supported | Real-time output streaming |\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## Dependencies\n636: \n637: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n638: |------------|---------|---------|\n639: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox` | Local | Sandbox interface (AR-009) |\n640: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Status persistence (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014) |\n641: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | Shared types |\n642: | `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | ExecutionID generation |\n643: \n644: ---\n645: \n646: ## File Index\n647: \n648: | Path | Purpose |\n649: |------|---------|\n650: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | CommandExecutor implementation |\n651: | `pkg/picod/executor_test.go` | Unit tests |\n652: | `pkg/picod/types.go` | Request/response type definitions |\n653: | `pkg/picod/status.go` | Execution status management |\n654: | `pkg/picod/output.go` | Output capture and streaming |\n655: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | Error type definitions |\n656: | `pkg/picod/validation.go` | Request validation logic |\n657: \n658: ---\n659: \n660: ## Constants\n661: \n662: | Constant | Value | Description |\n663: |----------|-------|-------------|\n664: | `defaultTimeout` | `30s` | Default execution timeout |\n665: | `maxConcurrentDefault` | `100` | Default concurrent execution limit |\n666: | `maxOutputSizeDefault` | `10MB` | Default max output capture size |\n667: | `outputBufferSizeDefault` | `4KB` | Default output buffer size |\n668: | `executionIDLength` | `16` | Length of generated execution IDs |\n669: \n670: ---\n671: \n672: ## Configuration\n673: \n674: ### Environment Variables\n675: \n676: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n677: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n678: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default timeout for command execution |\n679: | `PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT` | No | `100` | Maximum concurrent executions |\n680: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Maximum output capture size |\n681: | `PICOD_OUTPUT_BUFFER_SIZE` | No | `4KB` | Output buffer size for streaming |\n682: \n683: ---\n684: \n685: ## API Endpoints Summary\n686: \n687: This AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n688: \n689: | Consumer | Usage |\n690: |----------|-------|\n691: | Workload Manager | Execute commands in sandboxes |\n692: | CLI Toolkit | Synchronous command execution |\n693: | Integration Layer | Async execution with streaming |\n694: \n695: ---\n696: \n697: ## Migration Notes\n698: \n699: - **New dependencies**: Add `github.com/google/uuid` to go.mod\n700: - **Store dependency**: Requires working store (Redis/Valkey) for status persistence\n701: - **Sandbox dependency**: Requires functional sandbox interface (AR-009)\n702: - **No breaking changes**: PicoD API is additive layer on existing components\n703: \n704: ---\n705: \n706: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n707: \n708: 1. **Interface Completeness**: All CommandExecutor methods implemented\n709: 2. **Request Validation**: Invalid requests rejected before execution\n710: 3. **Resource Enforcement**: Resource limits enforced via sandbox integration\n711: 4. **Status Tracking**: State transitions persisted correctly\n712: 5. **Output Handling**: Stdout/stderr captured and streamable\n713: 6. **Cancellation**: Running executions can be cancelled\n714: 7. **Error Types**: Appropriate errors returned for each failure mode\n715: 8. **Context Handling**: Respects context cancellation\n716: 9. **Concurrency Limits**: Enforced and queued correctly\n717: 10. **Integration**: Works with sandbox (AR-009) and store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n\n(End of file - total 717 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-015  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe PicoD Command Execution API provides a high-level interface for executing commands in sandbox environments. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution, with features including resource limits, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CommandExecutor Interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `CommandExecutor` interface that supports synchronous execution, asynchronous execution, status retrieval, cancellation, and output streaming.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872073802,"end":1775872073842}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872073846,"sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3956cc001b1QjPXte17tQUW","messageID":"msg_d7a393afb001htqHlJh35Bi4lM","sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n6: \n7: ## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n8: \n9: - [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n10: - [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n11: - [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n12: - [ ] Document error codes and status states\n13: \n14: ## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n15: \n16: - [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n17: - [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n18: - [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n19: - [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n20: \n21: ## Phase 3: Output Handling\n22: \n23: - [ ] Design output capture mechanism\n24: - [ ] Implement stdout/stderr collection\n25: - [ ] Add output streaming support (buffer-based)\n26: - [ ] Handle large output scenarios\n27: \n28: ## Phase 4: Error Handling and Status\n29: \n30: - [ ] Implement execution status lifecycle\n31: - [ ] Add timeout and cancellation support\n32: - [ ] Design error translation layer\n33: - [ ] Add execution result metadata\n34: \n35: ## Phase 5: Testing\n36: \n37: - [ ] Write unit tests for execution logic\n38: - [ ] Create mock sandbox for testing\n39: - [ ] Add integration tests\n40: - [ ] Performance and resource limit tests\n41: \n42: ## Dependencies\n43: \n44: - AR-009: Sandbox orchestration system (for integration)\n45: - AR-012: Session storage interface (for status persistence)\n46: \n47: ## Estimated Timeline\n48: \n49: - Phase 1: 1 day\n50: - Phase 2: 1.5 days\n51: - Phase 3: 1 day\n52: - Phase 4: 0.5 day\n53: - Phase 5: 1 day\n54: \n55: Total: 4-5 days\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD command execution API.\n\n## Phase 1: API Design and Interface Definition\n\n- [ ] Define command execution request/response structures\n- [ ] Design PicoD client interface\n- [ ] Define execution options (timeout, resource limits, env vars)\n- [ ] Document error codes and status states\n\n## Phase 2: Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] Implement CommandExecutor struct and methods\n- [ ] Implement synchronous execution flow\n- [ ] Implement asynchronous execution with status tracking\n- [ ] Add resource limit integration points\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/plan.md","time":{"start":1775872073804,"end":1775872073845}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872073849,"sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","part":{"id":"prt_d7a395b8d001tl6cvZqm1qgglc","messageID":"msg_d7a393afb001htqHlJh35Bi4lM","sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Test Categories\n4: \n5: ### Unit Tests\n6: \n7: #### executor_test.go\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: // TestExecute_Success - Basic successful execution\n11: // TestExecute_Timeout - Execution timeout handling\n12: // TestExecute_ResourceLimit - Resource limit enforcement\n13: // TestExecute_InvalidCommand - Invalid command handling\n14: // TestExecute_SandboxError - Sandbox failure handling\n15: \n16: // TestExecuteAsync_Success - Basic async execution\n17: // TestExecuteAsync_QueueFull - Queue capacity handling\n18: // TestExecuteAsync_Cancellation - Async execution cancellation\n19: \n20: // TestGetStatus_Pending - Status retrieval for pending\n21: // TestGetStatus_Running - Status retrieval for running\n22: // TestGetStatus_Completed - Status retrieval for completed\n23: // TestGetStatus_NotFound - Non-existent execution\n24: \n25: // TestCancel_Running - Cancel running execution\n26: // TestCancel_Completed - Cancel already completed\n27: // TestCancel_NotFound - Cancel non-existent\n28: \n29: // TestStreamOutput_RealTime - Output streaming\n30: // TestStreamOutput_LargeOutput - Large output handling\n31: // TestStreamOutput_Closed - Stream closure handling\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Integration Tests\n35: \n36: #### executor_integration_test.go\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: // TestIntegration_EndToEnd - Full execution flow\n40: // TestIntegration_ConcurrentExecutions - Multiple parallel executions\n41: // TestIntegration_ResourceContention - Resource limit scenarios\n42: // TestIntegration_StatusPersistence - Status storage/retrieval\n43: // TestIntegration_CancellationRace - Race condition handling\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ### Mock Implementations\n47: \n48: ```go\n49: // MockSandboxClient - Mock sandbox for testing\n50: // MockStatusStore - Mock status storage\n51: // MockResourceLimiter - Mock resource limiting\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## Test Data\n55: \n56: ### Sample Commands\n57: \n58: ```go\n59: var testCommands = []struct {\n60:     name    string\n61:     command string\n62:     args    []string\n63:     wantErr bool\n64: }{\n65:     {\"echo\", \"echo\", []string{\"hello\"}, false},\n66:     {\"exit_0\", \"true\", nil, false},\n67:     {\"exit_1\", \"false\", nil, true},\n68:     {\"sleep\", \"sleep\", []string{\"0.1\"}, false},\n69:     {\"invalid\", \"__invalid_command__\", nil, true},\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### Resource Limit Test Cases\n74: \n75: ```go\n76: var resourceTests = []struct {\n77:     name      string\n78:     memory    int64\n79:     cpu       float64\n80:     wantLimit bool\n81: }{\n82:     {\"within_limits\", 1024 * 1024 * 100, 50.0, false},\n83:     {\"exceed_memory\", 1024 * 1024 * 1024, 50.0, true},\n84:     {\"exceed_cpu\", 1024 * 1024 * 100, 150.0, true},\n85: }\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ## Coverage Targets\n89: \n90: - Line coverage: >= 85%\n91: - Branch coverage: >= 80%\n92: - Critical paths: 100%\n93: \n94: ## Test Environment\n95: \n96: - Go 1.21+\n97: - Mock sandbox implementation\n98: - In-memory status store for unit tests\n99: - Docker-based sandbox for integration tests\n100: \n101: ## Test Execution\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: # Unit tests only\n105: go test ./pkg/picod/... -short\n106: \n107: # All tests including integration\n108: go test ./pkg/picod/...\n109: \n110: # With coverage\n111: go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n112: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n113: ```\n\n(End of file - total 113 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API - Test Specification\n\n## Test Categories\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### executor_test.go\n\n```go\n// TestExecute_Success - Basic successful execution\n// TestExecute_Timeout - Execution timeout handling\n// TestExecute_ResourceLimit - Resource limit enforcement\n// TestExecute_InvalidCommand - Invalid command handling\n// TestExecute_SandboxError - Sandbox failure handling\n\n// TestExecuteAsync_Success - Basic async execution\n// TestExecuteAsync_QueueFull - Queue capacity handling\n// TestExecuteAsync_Cancellation - Async execution cancellation\n\n// TestGetStatus_Pending - Status retrieval for pending","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tests.md","time":{"start":1775872073807,"end":1775872073846}}}}
