{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872320495,"sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","part":{"id":"prt_d7a39b7b8001khEJUbdijGUAVI","messageID":"msg_d7a397da8001ZFqU4H1UkAYF0Y","sessionID":"ses_285c6eb7bffesHDqSBGmAxReej","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","content":"# AR-015 вҖ” PicoD е‘Ҫд»Өжү§иЎҢ API (PicoD Command Execution API)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed вҶ’ ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-015 implements the PicoD command execution API providing synchronous and asynchronous command execution in sandbox environments. The API supports resource constraints, output streaming, execution cancellation, and persistent status tracking.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 вҖ” Type Definitions and Interfaces\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/picod/types.go` with `ExecutionID` type | File compiles; type defined as string alias | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Define `ExecutionRequest` struct with all fields (Command, Args, WorkingDir, Environment, Timeout, ResourceLimits, SessionID) | All fields match delta-spec; JSON tags present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Define `ExecutionResult` struct (ID, Status, ExitCode, Stdout, Stderr, StartedAt, FinishedAt, Error) | All fields match delta-spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Define `ExecutionStatus` struct (ID, State, StartedAt, FinishedAt, ExitCode) | Fields match delta-spec; pointers for optional | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Define `ExecutionState` type and constants (StatePending, StateRunning, StateCompleted, StateFailed, StateCancelled) | Constants have correct string values | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.6 | Define `ResourceConstraints` struct (MaxMemory, MaxCPU, MaxIOBytes, MaxFiles) | Types match spec (int64, float64, int) | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.7 | Define `ExecutionError` struct (Code, Message, Details) | Code field is string type | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.8 | Define `OutputChunk` struct (Data, Type, Timestamp) and `OutputType` constants (Stdout, Stderr) | Types match spec | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.9 | Define `ExecutorOptions` struct (DefaultTimeout, MaxConcurrentExecutions, MaxOutputSize, OutputBufferSize) | All config fields present | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.10 | Define `CommandExecutor` interface with Execute, ExecuteAsync, GetStatus, Cancel, StreamOutput methods | Interface signature matches delta-spec | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All type definitions compile and match delta-spec exactly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 вҖ” Error Type Definitions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Create `pkg/picod/errors.go` with error variable definitions | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.2 | Define `ErrInvalidRequest` error | Error message: \"picod: invalid request\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.3 | Define `ErrInvalidCommand` error | Error message: \"picod: command is required\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.4 | Define `ErrInvalidSessionID` error | Error message: \"picod: session ID is required\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.5 | Define `ErrInvalidWorkingDir` error | Error message: \"picod: invalid working directory\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.6 | Define `ErrResourceExceeded` error | Error message: \"picod: resource limits exceeded\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.7 | Define `ErrTimeout` error | Error message: \"picod: execution timeout\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.8 | Define `ErrSandboxUnavailable` error | Error message: \"picod: sandbox unavailable\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.9 | Define `ErrExecutionFailed` error | Error message: \"picod: execution failed\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.10 | Define `ErrExecutionNotFound` error | Error message: \"picod: execution not found\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.11 | Define `ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete` error | Error message: \"picod: execution already complete\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.12 | Define `ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions` error | Error message: \"picod: too many concurrent executions\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.2.13 | Define `ErrCancelled` error | Error message: \"picod: execution cancelled\" | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All 13 error types defined and exportable.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 вҖ” Request Validation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Create `pkg/picod/validation.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.2 | Implement `ValidateRequest(req *ExecutionRequest) error` | Returns nil for valid request | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.3 | Validate empty command returns `ErrInvalidCommand` | Unit test: empty command rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.4 | Validate command path traversal detection (e.g., `../../../etc/passwd`) | Unit test: path traversal rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.5 | Validate empty SessionID returns `ErrInvalidSessionID` | Unit test: empty session ID rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.6 | Validate working directory against allowed paths | Unit test: invalid working dir rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.7 | Validate environment variable names (format checking) | Unit test: invalid env var names rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.8 | Validate ResourceConstraints values (non-negative) | Unit test: negative values rejected | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All validation rules implemented with unit tests.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 вҖ” CommandExecutor Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Create `pkg/picod/executor.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Define `executor` struct with dependencies (sandboxClient, store, options, concurrency controls) | All fields present | 1h |\n| 4.4.3 | Implement `NewExecutor(opts ExecutorOptions) (*executor, error)` constructor | Returns initialized executor | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.4 | Add `executionIDGenerator` method for unique ID generation | IDs match pattern `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$`, length 8-64 | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.5 | Add concurrency limit tracking (semaphore or channel) | Max concurrent tracked correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.6 | Add execution registry map for active executions | Map safely accessible (mutex protected) | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.7 | Add configuration from environment variables (PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT, PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE, PICOD_OUTPUT_BUFFER_SIZE) | Env vars parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Executor structure compiles with proper initialization.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 вҖ” Synchronous Execution (Execute)\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Implement `Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.2 | Validate request before execution | Invalid request returns error without sandbox call | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.3 | Resolve sandbox by SessionID | Query store for sandbox info | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.4 | Handle sandbox unavailable error | Returns `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.5 | Execute command in sandbox with timeout | Timeout enforced via context | 1h |\n| 4.5.6 | Capture stdout and stderr | Output captured in ExecutionResult | 1h |\n| 4.5.7 | Handle successful execution (exit code 0) | Returns result with ExitCode=0, nil error | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.8 | Handle failed execution (non-zero exit code) | Returns result with ExitCode!=0, ErrExecutionFailed | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.9 | Handle timeout during execution | Returns ErrTimeout, status StateFailed | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.10 | Handle context cancellation | Returns ErrCancelled | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.11 | Enforce output size limits | Output truncated at MaxOutputSize with indicator | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Execute method works for sync execution with all error cases.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 вҖ” Asynchronous Execution (ExecuteAsync)\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Implement `ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Validate request before queuing | Invalid request returns error immediately | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.3 | Generate unique ExecutionID | ID unique per execution | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.4 | Create initial ExecutionStatus with StatePending | Status persisted to store | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.5 | Queue execution for background processing | Execution added to queue/channel | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.6 | Return ExecutionID immediately | Does not wait for execution | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.7 | Handle queue full / max concurrent scenarios | Returns ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions or queues | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Async execution queues correctly and returns ID immediately.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 вҖ” Status Management\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Implement `GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.2 | Query status from store by ExecutionID | Returns stored status | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.3 | Return ErrExecutionNotFound for non-existent ID | Unit test: missing ID returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.4 | Implement status transition: Pending вҶ’ Running | Transition updates store | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.5 | Implement status transition: Running вҶ’ Completed | Transition updates store with FinishedAt | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.6 | Implement status transition: Running вҶ’ Failed | Transition updates store with ExitCode and Error | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.7 | Implement status transition: Running вҶ’ Cancelled | Transition updates store with FinishedAt | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.8 | Enforce terminal state immutability | Updates to terminal states rejected | 0.5h |\n| 4.7.9 | Persist status changes to store | Store.UpdateStatus called on changes | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Status lifecycle managed correctly with persistence.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 вҖ” Cancellation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Implement `Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Look up execution by ID | Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if not found | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Signal sandbox to terminate running process | Sandbox receives termination signal | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Update status to StateCancelled | Status updated in store | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.5 | Return ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete for terminal states | Cannot cancel completed execution | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.6 | Clean up resources on cancellation | Goroutines exit, channels close | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Cancellation stops execution and updates status correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.9 вҖ” Output Capture and Streaming\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.9.1 | Create `pkg/picod/output.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.2 | Implement `StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)` | Method signature matches interface | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.3 | Return ErrExecutionNotFound for non-existent execution | Unit test: missing ID returns error | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.4 | Create output channel for streaming | Channel returned correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.5 | Stream output chunks as they are produced | Chunks received in order | 1h |\n| 4.9.6 | Close channel when execution completes | Channel closed on completion | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.7 | Handle context cancellation in streaming | Channel closed, goroutine exits cleanly | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.8 | Implement output buffering with size limits | Buffer respects OutputBufferSize | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.9 | Separate stdout and stderr in OutputChunk.Type | Type field set correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.10 | Store output for later retrieval | Output persisted to store for completed executions | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Output streaming works with proper lifecycle management.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.10 вҖ” Sandbox Integration\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.10.1 | Create `pkg/picod/sandbox_client.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.2 | Define `SandboxClient` interface for sandbox operations | Interface defined | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.3 | Implement sandbox resolution by SessionID | Query store for sandbox endpoint | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.4 | Implement command execution call to sandbox | Request sent to sandbox | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.5 | Merge environment variables (request overrides sandbox defaults) | Env vars merged correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.6 | Pass ResourceConstraints to sandbox | Limits applied in sandbox | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.7 | Handle sandbox connection failures | Returns ErrSandboxUnavailable with details | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.8 | Handle sandbox execution errors | Errors translated appropriately | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Sandbox integration layer works with AR-009 interface.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.11 вҖ” Store Integration\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.11.1 | Implement status persistence on state changes | store.UpdateStatus called | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.2 | Handle store failures gracefully | Log error, continue (documented limitation) | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.3 | Persist execution output for completed executions | Output stored in store | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.4 | Retrieve execution status from store | GetStatus queries store | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Store integration works with AR-012/AR-013/AR-014 interface.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.12 вҖ” Unit Tests вҖ” Core Types\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.12.1 | Write `TestExecutionState_String` | Constants have correct values | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.2 | Write `TestExecutionRequest_ValidationScenarios` | Table-driven validation tests | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.3 | Write `TestExecutionResult_Struct` | Struct fields accessible | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.4 | Write `TestOutputChunk_Types` | Stdout/Stderr types correct | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Type tests pass with 100% coverage on types.go.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.13 вҖ” Unit Tests вҖ” Validation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.13.1 | Write `TestValidateRequest_EmptyCommand` | Returns ErrInvalidCommand | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.2 | Write `TestValidateRequest_PathTraversal` | Returns error for ../../../etc/passwd | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.3 | Write `TestValidateRequest_EmptySessionID` | Returns ErrInvalidSessionID | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.4 | Write `TestValidateRequest_InvalidWorkingDir` | Returns ErrInvalidWorkingDir | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.5 | Write `TestValidateRequest_InvalidEnvVarName` | Returns error for invalid env var names | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.6 | Write `TestValidateRequest_ValidRequest` | Returns nil for valid request | 0.5h |\n| 4.13.7 | Write `TestValidateRequest_InvalidResourceConstraints` | Returns error for negative values | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Validation tests pass with >90% coverage on validation.go.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.14 вҖ” Unit Tests вҖ” Execute (Sync)\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.14.1 | Write `TestExecute_Success` | Returns result with ExitCode=0 | 1h |\n| 4.14.2 | Write `TestExecute_InvalidRequest` | Returns error without sandbox call | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.3 | Write `TestExecute_Timeout` | Returns ErrTimeout | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.4 | Write `TestExecute_SandboxUnavailable` | Returns ErrSandboxUnavailable | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.5 | Write `TestExecute_NonZeroExitCode` | Returns ErrExecutionFailed with exit code | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.6 | Write `TestExecute_ContextCancelled` | Returns ErrCancelled | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.7 | Write `TestExecute_OutputSizeLimit` | Output truncated at limit | 0.5h |\n| 4.14.8 | Write `TestExecute_CapturesStdoutAndStderr` | Both streams captured separately | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Execute tests pass with mocked sandbox.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.15 вҖ” Unit Tests вҖ” ExecuteAsync\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.15.1 | Write `TestExecuteAsync_Success` | Returns unique ExecutionID | 1h |\n| 4.15.2 | Write `TestExecuteAsync_InvalidRequest` | Returns error, no ID generated | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.3 | Write `TestExecuteAsync_InitialStatusPending` | Status stored with StatePending | 0.5h |\n| 4.15.